The subject provides an overview of the aims and principles of musical activities in accordance with the national curriculum. Teaching methods and possibilities of teaching musical activities at pre-schol age. The subject deals with the possibilities of implementing musical activities in group work and connecting music with other subject areasObjectives/eesmärkid:  To provide an overview of child's musical development,the essence and importance of teaching of rhythm in comprehensive development of children and possibilities of musical development at pre-school age. To teach planning and conducting of musical activities at pre-school age.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student having completed the subject: 1) knows the goals and the content of music teaching in the national curriculum and is able to plan and conduct musical activities at pre-school age in accordance with the curriculum; 2) can implement correct teaching methods bearing in mind the integration of different fields and the principles of educational activities in the national curriculum; 3) has a complete overview of child's musical education at pre-school age.
